African Financial Crisis¶

by Huda Abd El-Majeed¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This Dataset specifically focuses on the Banking, Debt, Financial, Inflation and Systemic Crises that occurred, from 1860 to 2014, in 13 African countries, including: Algeria, Angola, Central African Republic, Ivory Coast, Egypt, Kenya, Mauritius, Morocco, Nigeria, South Africa, Tunisia, Zambia and Zimbabwe.

Define¶

  • Replace the 'systemic_crisis', 'currency_crises', 'inflation_crises' values to Crisis and No Crisis instead of 1 and 0

Code¶

In [16]:
cleaned_df['banking_crisis'].replace({'crisis': 'Crisis', 'no_crisis': 'No Crisis'}, inplace=True)
In [17]:
columns = ['systemic_crisis', 'currency_crises', 'inflation_crises']
cleaned_df[columns] = cleaned_df[columns].replace({0: 'No Crisis', 1: 'Crisis'})

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

There are 13 countries in the dataset with 10 features(systemic, currency, inflation and banking crises, exch usd , domestic debt, sovereign external debt, gdp weighted, inflation annual cpi and independence) and 1055 entries after cleaning.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

Inflation annual cpi is the main feature and i am interested in figuring out the other main features and their effects on every country crisis

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

I expect that domestic debt and sovereign external debt also have an effect on the occurrence of the different crises in the countries.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. How did the feature(s) of interest vary with other features in the dataset?¶

According to the different distributions, there is a strong relationship between the increasing of inflation CPI and the occurrence of various crises (Inflation Crises, Currency Crisis) and it's clearly shown in the relationship between the african countries with the inflation CPI rate and the different crises.

Did you observe any interesting relationships between the other features (not the main feature(s) of interest)?¶

Yes, The relationship between countries and the various crises. The No crisis cases is much higher than the crisis occurrence cases.

There is a strong relationship between systemic and banking crisis more than the inflation CPI rate and the banking crisis.

The relationship between that the country is being Sovereign External Indebted and the Banking crisis occurrence is not that strong.
